## Common Pitfalls

| Pitfall | Prevention |
|---------|------------|
| Submodule imports parent addon code | Never. Submodules are standalone. LLMs: check every `from` / `import` line. |
| Copy-pasting code during abstraction | Never copy from source addon. Recreate from scratch using the original as behavioral reference only. |
| Modifying production addon before submodule is tested | Never. Original code stays untouched until both headless and manual test gates pass. |
| Junction not followed by zip builder | Verified working. `shutil.copytree` and `blender extension build` both follow junctions. |
| Forgot `git init` | Each submodule and dev addon is its own repo. Init immediately after scaffolding. |
| Duplicate `bl_idname` across submodules | Namespace operators: `<ctx>.lks_<module>_<action>` — include the module name. |
| Panel doesn't appear in addon | Check that `register_addon.py` auto-discovers it. The submodule's `__init__.py` must exist and expose `register`/`unregister`. |
| Hot reload doesn't pick up changes | The `__init__.py` deep-reload walks `sys.modules` and reloads deepest-first. Junction-loaded modules are reloaded the same way. |
| `.gitignore` missing in submodule | Template includes one. If missing, create manually — at minimum ignore `__pycache__/`. |
| Dev code shipped to users | Ensure `dev/` is in both `.remoteignore` and `blender_manifest.toml` `paths_exclude_pattern`. The template configures this by default. |
| Public module imports from `dev/` | Never. Dependency is one-way: `dev/` imports from the addon, not the reverse. If `dev/` is absent, nothing should break. |

